My thoughts on Omnath, to bring us back an hour:

The Good:
• There isn't currently a Temur Lands Matter Commander
• There aren't very many playable Temur Commanders, period.
• It's flexible enough that you don't have to lands matter, and can roll right into elementals or do a hybrid of both.

The Bad:
• It doesn't feel very Temur? Maybe I'm just associating it with _Khans_ specific Temur tendencies, but isn't the whole idea of the wedge to care about big creatures and gain advantage from them? This is literally the first Temur commander since Intet to not care about creatures.
• I feel like we've explored Lands Matter thoroughly enough these days? Would have been nice to see a more general commander or something people have been clamoring for, rather than just ever-expanding lands into more color combinations. White is now the only color to not care about lands, and I'm fully expecting a Naya or Bant commander soon that's just land tax on a stick but broken in half. I dunno though, maybe I'm the only one that's kind of tired of lands matters.
